main event: A bank teller observed an object with possible wings and three lights over Syracuse, New York on January 5, 1966.
interesting points: The observation lasted for 10 seconds., The object was reported to move erratically., The sighting was made using binoculars from about 1000 yards away., The sky was described as dark and clear with many stars., The object was speculated to resemble an aircraft.
sighted object: an object with possible wings and three lights
